name: OpenAIModel

input.content: What port has 5 pins on the top and 4 on the bottom?

output: The description of a connector with 5 pins on the top and 4 on the bottom seems to match the USB 3.0 Micro-B connector. This connector is designed to support the SuperSpeed data transfer mode of USB 3.0. The USB 3.0 Micro-B connector is distinct from the more common Micro-USB (USB 2.0) connectors, as it has an additional set of pins beside the standard Micro-USB pin arrangement to handle the increased data transfer speed. This is why it has a wider appearance with one side featuring 5 pins (the SuperSpeed contacts) and the other side featuring the standard Micro-USB configuration of 4 pins. This type of connector is often found on external hard drives and some high-end smartphones and tablets from the early 2010s.
